Pinchbottom is a theatrical [[burlesque]] company created by [[Jonny Porkpie]] and [[Nasty Canasta]] in 2004 and run by Porkpie since 2010.<ref>http://www.pinchbottom.com/about/</ref> It is known for its brand of "theater-burlesque fusion" <ref>https://www.facebook.com/notes/burlesque-magazine/review-pinchbottoms-pretençión/100343864554</ref> which presents "full-length comedic play[s] in which performers take their clothes off in every other scene.".<ref>http://www.tor.com/blogs/2009/05/pinchbottom-dystopia-interview</ref>
==Awards== The group was awarded the first-ever "Most Innovative" trophy for their performance at The Burlesque Hall of Fame in 2007,<ref>http://www.burlesquehall.com/2007lineup/</ref> and named the "Best Burlesque" in New York by New York Magazine in 2007.<ref>http://nymag.com/bestofny/fun/2007/28818/</ref>
